President Obama has announced his intent to nominate Karen Brevard Stewart as Ambassador to the Republic of the Marshall Islands and Robert Riley as Ambassador to the Federated States of Micronesia. He also announced his intent to appoint Jaime Castillo as Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at the Department of Housing and Urban Development. Stewart is currently serving as Political Advisor to the Vice Chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, while Riley is serving as Management Counselor at the U.S. Embassy in Jakarta. Castillo is currently Acting Assistant Secretary for Public Affairs at HUD.